<p style="text-align:justify;">The Persians sacrificed part of their drink to the Gods, prayed to the Devil &#8211; sung battle Hymns, and married their nearest relations.  The Armenians had their houses under ground, and fastened hurdles to their feet to prevent them sinking in the snow.  The Israelites prepared themselves by fasting in order to see visions &#8211; in mourning and affliction they tore their clothes &#8211; nor would they approach a woman to uncover her nakedness whilst apart for her unclean<span class="AddHand-author">li</span>ness.  The Greeks resembled the Indians in the following instances &#8211; O soft in temper, says the King of men to his brother, What pity has seized thy soul, Menelaus?  Let none from destruction escape, none chide the death in our hands &#8211; not the lisping infant in the Mother's arms; not he shall escape with life.  Patroclus's funeral.  With their shorn locks they covered the dead &#8211; when they came to the destined</p>

